column14: Got a wonderful note yesterday from a true American hero— Antonio J Cruz, a former New York City police lieutenant who was at Ground Zero on 911. Mr Cruz appreciated House passage of the 9-11 victims bill.

I had the privilege of meeting Jimmy’s family earlier this year to hear firsthand their concerns for his safety, and about their efforts to ensure his care. Today, I grieve with them and recommit to preventing any further injustices.
Jimmy died tragically yesterday of a diabetic crisis. His death could have and should have been prevented, as his deportation was essentially a death sentence.

The skills and credentials to succeed in today’s economy must be attainable for working families. Yesterday I was proud to introduce the America’s College Promise Act, which will transform higher education by making available two years of free community college. #ACP2019  https://t.co/crHo2AqK0h

We have to make sure that the skills and credentials necessary to be successful in today’s economy are attainable for working families. Proud to introduce the America's College Promise Act with @SenatorBaldwin today. #ForThePeople

Enough with the thoughts and prayers, we need new laws. The House of Representatives passed #HR8, the Bipartisan Background Checks Act months ago, and Senate Majority Leader McConnell has refused to bring it for a vote. The Senate must act, NOW! #EnoughIsEnough  https://t.co/KeaogHW9wq
“Black families need @USPS.” ➡️  https://t.co/1Fi3P2z2aV

Honored to meet and sign this #GoldStar father's #KIA flag honoring his son, Special Agent Sergeant Joseph Peters, who died on October 6, 2013. We discussed ways to help #GoldStar families.  https://t.co/Y7KezGb2JD
In the wake of recent horrendous tragedies in our nation, it is so important that we pray for the victims and their families.

Mass shootings are becoming more frequent, and more deadly. I strongly support expanding background checks, but we have to face facts: deadly weapons of war, military-style rifles, have no place on our streets. We need bold action.  https://t.co/K4kTn1Qen0

This is a tragic case. We deserve a government that acts with compassion and decency, and that considers the consequences of its actions. These callous deportations must stop.   https://t.co/2VgQ2TWm8r
My heart goes out to the victims of this appalling crime. I thank the first responders for their quick action.  https://t.co/SIleUit87y

We’re not the only country where people play violent video games, and we’re not the only country which urgently needs to invest more in mental health. We ARE the only developed country where mass shootings are routine, and where gun violence kills so many. 2/3
My statement on the tragic terrorist attack in El Paso, and the shooting in Dayton.  https://t.co/X71HbMyYIR

Deeply saddened by the tragic news from Gilroy. My heart goes out to all impacted. We can’t continue to accept these appalling tragedies without action. The House has passed major gun violence legislation—the Senate must follow suit.

Over and over, the house has passed concrete legislation to help American families and to strengthen our country. Mitch McConnell isn’t interested in solutions, negotiation or real legislation.  https://t.co/Q6vhC4vTl2
LGBTQ rights are human rights. This case is tragic and appalling.  https://t.co/P92QaCmqWC

These services not only help families by providing a safe place for children during the day, but it is also one of the smartest investments we can make. I am so pleased that Head Start of Rockland can continue to foster the growth of our future leaders.

These massacres aren’t happening in other industrialized nations around the world. I’m outraged that the Senate, led by Mitch McConnell, doesn’t find it necessary to bring common sense gun violence prevention legislation to the Senate floor to help end these senseless killings.

Prayers from politicians can’t bring back the victims or heal the families in El Paso and Dayton. They deserve action and a commitment to bringing these mass killings to an end.   The worst five mass shootings in the United States’ history have all occurred since 2016.
My heart breaks for the communities forced to endure these tragedies.   The gun violence epidemic in this country must end.

50 years ago, families across the globe huddled to witness Neil Armstrong & Buzz Aldrin’s historic “leap”. As we celebrate #Apollo50th, we are reminded of the American innovation that led to mankind’s first lunar landing but also look forward to returning to continue the journey.  https://t.co/z4DNnV1UTj

Tonight the House repealed the Cadillac Tax- #Obamacare's penalizing 40% tax on employer-provided health care coverage. As a cosponsor of The Middle Class Health Benefits Tax Repeal Act, I was proud to support America's workforce and their families.  https://t.co/FDFeEY95tE

After the El Paso shooting, I joined 47 members of Congress to call on House & Senate leaders to take immediate action to address the threat of white supremacist terrorism. Republicans & Democrats have a chance to come together & do good work for millions of Americans. (1/2)
It is dereliction of duty for the Senate to remain in recess while our communities live in fear of the next mass shooting. (3/3)

Our communities cannot continue to grieve while Sen. McConnell refuses to allow a vote on commonsense bills to address gun violence. In the 162 days since the House passed a bill requiring universal background checks, 196 lives have been lost to mass shootings in America. (2/3)
It is a time to keep our current servicemembers in our thoughts, as they expose themselves to the line of fire to ensure we can continue to enjoy our freedom. (2/2)

Today is National Purple Heart Day. The Purple Heart is a military decoration that honors the brave men and women who were killed or wounded while serving our country. On this day, we remember their sacrifice and valor. (1/2)  https://t.co/5TfO6ddu8E

I am saddened for all those impacted by the mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio. Virginia Beach knows your pain all too well. Americans must band together, help each other, and do all we can to combat the gun violence epidemic we are facing.

My heart goes out to all affected by the mass shooting in El Paso. Our Virginia Beach community is recovering from a similarly horrific incident. My team & I stand ready to help those in need & fight back against the gun violence epidemic hurting America.  https://t.co/RzMcXdniKD

#TBT to May when I introduced a bill to repeal a tax hike on Gold Star Families. These families made the ultimate sacrifice & it broke my heart when a surviving spouse alerted me to the problem. I had to act and was proud to introduce this bipartisan bill.  https://t.co/NkrrrkzbOz

Keith sacrificed his life to save others during the May 31 shooting in Virginia Beach.   I hope the President quickly signs this bill into law so we can properly remember a true hero. This is our chance to showcase Keith's bravery to our community, Commonwealth, and nation. (2/2)
It was fantastic to hear Chief Boone's thoughts about reducing violence in Norfolk. I look forward to working with him and the other Hampton Roads chiefs and sheriffs to make our communities safer.

These amendments would eliminate unfair taxes on those who teach our military children and keep a spotlight on important research for wound care for our troops. I will continue to proudly fight for and find new ways to serve our servicemembers and as well as their families.(2/2)

Servicemembers and their families are the backbone of Virginia and it’s an honor to advocate for them. I praise the House for approving two of my amendments to the National Defense Authorization Act to help these brave men & women and their families.(1/2) https://t.co/ww67MwsBQN

I recently was inspired by a group of @NFL players with Hampton Roads ties who volunteered to give food to children in need. It was heartwarming to see the football players help their community and make a positive difference.  https://t.co/rtgkbRZ14w

Congress should honor the legacy of our fallen service members by putting Gold Star children in the best position to succeed. I’m proud to work in a bipartisan way to recognize the bravery of fallen servicemembers and their families. (1/2)

Wonderful to see the 380th Army Band out of Fort Eustis play for WWII vet Mort Gustoff. Mr. Gustoff fought valiantly in the Battle of the Bulge and hoped to see a fife & drum band play on July 4 but was unable. I was heartened by the band's tribute to him.  https://t.co/VJn1OGaMqH

The House has passed the bipartisan Rehabilitation for Multi-Employer Pensions Act. This bill would provide financial assistance to critical & declining pension plans, ensuring retirees receive their hard-earned benefits. I will continue to fight for our #VA02 working families!  https://t.co/z1c6B8XaMv

I am saddened by the passing of Chris Kraft – a Hampton native "who helped chart a course from the Earth to the Moon." Kraft was a decorated NASA legend who will leave behind a huge legacy. My thoughts are with his family and his loved ones.  https://t.co/rsfsK6uawY #VA02

Great to speak at the North End Waterfront Residents Association monthly meeting about climate change, impeachment, gun control, the ongoing issues on the southern border and other topics that directly affect the North End and the 8th Congressional District.  https://t.co/bWdFr1Sz5s
Boston Herald: Mass shootings require real action  https://t.co/DKHXLcQ8L8

(3/3) Congress has debated and considered several Bills to strengthen America’s gun control laws – it is now time up to take up commonsense solutions to prevent more innocent lives from being taken by gun violence.

(2/3) We are now left with the reality that America has experienced two mass shootings within 24 hours – taking 29 innocent lives. There is a gun violence epidemic being fueled by hate throughout our country and it is well past the time to act.

(1/3) This morning America woke up horrified to hear about another senseless mass shooting that occurred in Dayton, Ohio last night, taking nine innocent lives.  I pray for their families, friends and all those impacted by this sickening act of hate.
(3/3) Congress must take every common sense measure to prevent the use of high capacity weapons and munitions in these mass shootings. We must act now.

(2/3) The people of El Paso have been generous and compassionate in their support for the humane treatment of immigrant families. We continue to pray for their strength and resilience in the aftermath of this horrific act of hate.

(1/3) Our thoughts and prayer go out to the people of the City of El Paso and the victims of the horrific mass shooting yesterday. Thank you to all the first responders and law enforcement officials for your swift and courageous response that undoubtedly saved many lives.

Scathing report from @OversightDems second interim staff report regarding Jared Kushner’s apparent effort to sell Nuclear Technology to Saudi Arabia in exchange for financial assistance for his families’ bankrupt high-rise office tower in NYC.  https://t.co/KLrVnPETfd

Americans have had enough of the violence. They’ve had enough of thoughts & prayers. They’ve had enough of the inaction.  It’s been over 160 days since I voted to pass bipartisan gun safety legislation- & still, the Senate’s refused to act. It’s time they #DoSomething & end this.

The El Paso shooter said his attack was to fight the “Hispanic invasion of Texas.”   *Invasion* - a word we’ve heard so many times from President Trump. This rhetoric is dangerous, and it needs to stop.  https://t.co/AiNoUnoggb

Three mass shootings in one week. You can’t just keep tweeting about this, Leader McConnell.   We passed gun safety legislation and you’re the one blocking it. If you don’t have enough backbone to step up and keep Americans safe, who do you even serve? #NotOneMore

Only a week after a mass shooting in California, we’re seeing yet another in Texas. This is an epidemic in America & it needs to end.   I stand with El Paso & all the folks in America who want their government to act to keep families safe.

Yesterday, @ICEgov conducted its largest raid in a decade & tore hundreds of families apart. This Admin's actions are deliberately cruel and meant to send a message of fear into our immigrant communities. We can’t turn our backs to this suffering. We need immigration reform NOW.

Last night’s panic in Times Square is chilling & shows Americans live in constant fear of another shooting or violent attack. #ThisIsAmerica, but it doesn’t have to be. The Senate must take action immediately to #EndGunViolence.

“A writer’s life and work are not a gift to mankind; they are its necessity.”   Today we lost an American legend whose powerful worlds inspired many. I’m so saddened to hear of Toni Morrison’s passing and send my deepest condolences to her family.   https://t.co/6KsfNhFnet

A harrowing insight into the lives of separated migrant children who are still unsure of their futures and the likelihood of being reunited with their loved ones. I condemn family separation and will never quit fighting to #keepfamiliestogether.  https://t.co/PY9ft4bQh2

@BhaskarK_ @MomsDemand @GiffordsCourage @sandyhook How would a another red flag law or another background check law have prevented the sandy hook shooting? I’m upset that today’s legislators aren’t proposing serious solutions.

@snarkysnowqueen I’m offended by politicians who are offering so-called solutions that have nothing to do with those tragedies while pretending they do. For instance, can you relate the push for “universal background checks” to those shootings?
If you think “universal background checks” are a good thing and can be enforced without a “universal gun registry,”  bless your heart.

Source:  “Based on recovered shell casings, he [police chief Biehl] said Betts fired at least 41 rounds before police officers responded, shooting 58 rounds at him near the entrance to a Dayton nightclub.”   https://t.co/o9rChef0F7

Some have asked, “who needs 100 rounds?”  If 6 brave, trained, and alert police officers with professionally maintained weapons fired 58 rounds to subdue the Dayton shooter,  I’d say my wife deserves at least that many chances to protect herself and my kids when I’m not home.

I joined @RMConservative​ on his podcast yesterday. In this episode, we discuss popular gun control proposals and conclude that these measures would not have stopped the recent El Paso and Dayton mass shootings and will not prevent future attacks.    https://t.co/AWzFTEdnda

1. Shootings keep occurring in places where civilians are banned from having guns, 2. almost any modern firearm can be used to inflict mass casualties and 3. armed citizens prevent many attacks from becoming mass public shootings.
Media bias has a huge impact on the gun control debate. The entire debate would be dramatically different if at least three points about mass public shootings ever got coverage...

The Army Corps wants to hear your thoughts as they seek immediate change to the management of Lake Okeechobee for the next several years - including minimizing discharges when there are harmful algal blooms on Lake O to protect public health. Learn more:  https://t.co/rfhmngOY6a

Amazing to spend National Night Out across #Sacramento with neighbors in our vibrant communities. In #Sac, our sense of togetherness is a bond that keeps us strong in the face of the tragedy. We have each others' backs.   https://t.co/17s7UjrSBA

Sacramento remains a city that is committed to artistic expression. When words don’t seem like enough or when our thoughts are too difficult to say, art acts as a universal language that allows us to share what’s in our hearts.  https://t.co/CDcaqHnphu

Our hearts break for those killed and those whose lives will never be the same. Gilroy, El Paso, Dayton - 3 mass killings in 8 days and 2 within 24 hours of each other. Families are demanding action and accountability.  https://t.co/Got7VuT0PX

I was sickened by what I saw at the border. Migrants were crammed in holding cells w/o drinking water or showers. Many are in unsanitary conditions w/o proper medical care, & we cannot let this stand. Today, I voted to end these conditions & get migrant children & families care.

Women of color are more likely to be low-wage workers. The #RaiseTheWageAct will give 1 in 3 women workers a boost in their paychecks, including 41% black women, & 38% of Latinas, helping them better provide for themselves & their families!

Proud that my bill, the SOFFA Act, advanced out of the @EnergyCommerce Committee. By adopting CA furniture flammability standards, we can help keep unsafe toxic chemicals out of everyday household furniture and away from children and families.

Sister Norma – "This is not a political issue. This is a humanitarian issue. It's about protecting people. We should be a country that helps resolve and stop the abuse of these families that are coming in search of safety and protection."  https://t.co/WYDjheG5cQ

1/ More than 130 million Americans live with a pre-existing condition. If Republicans’ Texas v. U.S. lawsuit succeeds, they’ll be once again left at the mercy of insurance companies. Here's what ACA repeal means for California families. #ProtectOurCare  https://t.co/jCHMTNFpQv

No child should know that pain or trauma. They deserve dignity, care, and compassion. My heart breaks for the 30 children remaining at the Clint Border Patrol Station and the hundreds more who have continually been deprived of the basic care every child needs and deserves.

I will fight alongside my colleagues to hold Trump accountable and reunite families so children can get back to living a healthy and normal life. No child should be separated from their family.  https://t.co/yCpBBKLjb4

Last night, @thecityofsac lost a bright and talented member of the police force. Officer Tara O'Sullivan was tragically shot in the line of duty defending and protecting our city. We all grieve for the O'Sullivan family and the Sacramento police community.  https://t.co/jhSHeh8mJr

No one in this country should fear going shopping or going out on a Saturday night. These monsters acted out of pure hate—we must not allow this evil to ever happen again.  All Americans lift up the families who are mourning, & we thank the first responders who acted so quickly.  https://t.co/fjugpRw5jg

Because of Rep @ConawayTX11's steady leadership, Republicans passed a historic farm bill last year that was good for farmers, ranchers, and families⁠—and it helped move more Americans from welfare to work.

Next we held an emotional and powerful meeting with the mother and family of Berta Cáceres, a human rights activist who was murdered for her work to protect her indigenous land and the environment.  Justice must be done!  https://t.co/TuQ8cwbzWE

9/ To understand the violence and poverty in El Salvador that drives families out in search of safety, we need to look through the eyes of those who flee and acknowledge that America has a moral obligation to help them given our history in the region.  https://t.co/YaEpuSAuOf
7/ Reagan and Bush Administration officials routinely turned a blind eye to the torture, disappearances and murders like those of the Jesuit priests which were carried out by the Salvadoran military.

6/ And even worse, it was just the latest atrocity committed by Salvadoran troops who had received extensive U.S. military training, including the El Mozote massacre where over 1,000 people were killed — mostly women and children.   https://t.co/bW37UupWZ0

5/ What I discovered was deeply disturbing: not only did the high command of the Salvadoran military give the orders, but 19 of the 26 members of the unit that committed the murders had received U.S. taxpayer-funded training at the U.S. Army School of the Americas.

3/ Fathers Ignacio Ellacuria, “Nacho” Martin-Baro, Segundo Montes, Juan Ramon Moreno, Joaquin Lopez y Lopez, and Amando Lopez were killed for speaking out against a terrible war and standing up for the poor and marginalized.  https://t.co/2msc5a2H5m

2/ We visited the chapel where the priests are buried. Then we visited the rose garden which is the memorial where 4 of the 6 priests were murdered.   We also visited the rooms where Elba and Celina were murdered so there would be no witnesses to these heinous crimes.  https://t.co/Tk30AN8zp0

1/ Today our delegation visited the University of Central America in El Salvador, where 6 Jesuit Priests, their housekeeper Elba Ramos, and her daughter Celina Ramos were brutally murdered on November 16, 1989 by the U.S.-backed Salvadoran military.  https://t.co/WY7x6ty1JC

Please join me in praying for the full recovery of #NC10 native & @NCSHP Trooper, Christopher Wooten, who was critically injured during a police chase on Monday. This incident reminds us of the sacrifices our law enforcement make each day to keep us safe→  https://t.co/42LLNPpH1u

Yesterday, the @FinancialCmte held a hearing on @facebook’s Project Libra. I had the opportunity to share my thoughts on supporting financial innovation & to ask questions on how this plan will comply with existing regulation →  https://t.co/HIPdARJLWU

My heart breaks for the grieving families and communities in #TX and #OH. I’m anxious for more answers, and like so many Americans, I’m angry. As we wait to learn more, one fact is clear—violence motivated by white nationalism is terrorism. It’s evil & has no place here.

The senseless gun violence that plagues our nation is unacceptable. Continuing to send thoughts & prayers after #Dayton, #ElPaso & other tragedies is not enough. The GOP-led Senate must follow the House & immediately pass common sense gun safety legislation. Enough is enough!

Unconscionable for the Trump admin. to end critical programs that seek to reunite #Haitians & #Filipino World War II #veterans in the US with their family members. Further illustrates the President's anti-immigrant agenda & practice of separating families.  https://t.co/aRgrYyZYIg

@Campaign4Kids @CASAforall @CHIRLA @GPIWCenter @HispanicFed @nakasec @npnewamericans @SAALTweets @weareoneamerica My legislation is the companion to the Senate bill led by @SenSchumer, @SenJeffMerkley, @SenFeinstein, @SenatorDurbin & @PattyMurray. @realDonaldTrump's lack of empathy & compassion for kids & families at the border is unconscionable and demands action by Congress. 2/2

column14: Proud to introduce the “Stop Cruelty to Migrant Children Act” which seeks to ensure that migrant children & families who arrive at the U.S.-Mexico #border are provided with safe, sanitary & humane services. Details:  https://t.co/dqVeg1DLbx. #KeepFamiliesTogether 1/2  https://t.co/TVtfj5HIA1

Congratulations to Kyle Bragg on becoming @32BJSEIU’s president! Kyle has a long track record of fighting for working families and improving the lives of all workers. I wish him success, and I look forward to working together. #Queens

Sad about the passing of John Paul Stevens. He gave so much of his life to serving our nation, first in World War II and then as a Supreme Court Justice. A great legal mind, he made immense contributions to our nation. My thoughts and prayers are with his loved ones.

Heartbroken to hear the news coming out of El Paso. Our Orlando community stands in solidarity with its residents and the victims. It’s past time to do something about gun violence in this country. Failure to act will lead to more innocent lives lost.

You spoke, we listened. Today’s Family Friendly Town Hall in #Orlando will take place on a weekend so working families like yours also have the opportunity to share your concerns with me. Hope you can join us.  https://t.co/EIkY6988qz

Couldn’t make our town hall today in #Sanford? We have two more coming up, including a family friendly one this Saturday for working families who can’t attend our weekday events.   More info ⬇️   https://t.co/iY87d4dTT5

HAPPENING WEDNESDAY ⬇️  All #FL07 seniors and their families are invited to join us at this town hall in #Sanford.   For more details and to RSVP, click here:  https://t.co/ZLEFeF3YkM  https://t.co/pcAkpbW8Pp

I invite #FL07 seniors, veterans, and families in Orange & Seminole counties to come to one of these three town hall meetings to share what’s on your minds so that I can take your concerns back to our nation’s capital. #FlaPol  RSVP here:  https://t.co/ZLEFeF3YkM  https://t.co/j6I7lv5jCN
I hope this continues to be a productive process that will lead to an agreement that improves the lives of American families, consumers, and workers. #NAFTA #USMCA #AMLO

I’m honored to have been part of the House effort to #RaiseTheWage & achieve a win for working families. In the United States Senate, and in state capitals across this country, our fight goes on. #FightFor15    https://t.co/LDMJkMkqpV

The House is on the verge of passing a minimum wage increase for the first time in over a decade. Proud of the incremental & the data-focused approach I helped negotiate which will help more hard-working families earn the pay they deserve.  #RaiseTheWage  https://t.co/aUhsyrkboS

A new @USCBO report estimates that raising the min. wage will give up to 27 million workers a raise & lift 1.3 million American workers out of poverty. As a proud cosponsor of the #RaisetheWage Act, I’ll keep fighting so all hard-working American families can earn a living wage.  https://t.co/Nc0RCRxIIZ

The time has come for Congress to reclaim its constitutional authority over trade. I intro’d a bill to strengthen congressional involvement in tariff decisions. Working families shouldn’t have to pay for the president’s reckless use of tariff authority.  https://t.co/JsURphWldq  https://t.co/qwb0IBFf6K

#Pulse was the deadliest attack against #LGBTQ+ people in U.S. history. As we celebrate #Pride Month, we must honor the victims' memories, be inspired by their legacies, & recognize the positive contributions the #LGBTQ+ community offers to the world.  https://t.co/djx9VTncDl

3 years since we lost 49 innocent lives to an act of hate at the #Pulse nightclub in #Orlando. Today we cherish their memories, honor their legacies, and pledge to do everything in our power to never let a tragedy like this happen again. #OrlandoUnited #OrlandoStrong  https://t.co/nWQStl6HOZ

As a member of the US Military Academy Board of Visitors, I mourn the death of Cadet Morgan. My thoughts are w/his loved ones & the tight-knit West Point community. Its a reminder of the risks officers-in-training take as they prepare to defend our nation  https://t.co/zGyoCIc5x1

Proud to join @repdarrensoto & @repvaldemings in introducing legislation that would designate #Pulse as a National Memorial Site. The love that the 49 victims brought into this world will always be stronger than the hate that stole their lives on that day. #OrlandoStrong  https://t.co/OzWzLdphet

Families across Florida, especially those who lost a loved one in the Pulse or Parkland shootings, live every day with the pain & loss caused by gun violence. The House has taken action to save lives. The Senate must do the same. #WearOrange #EndGunViolence  https://t.co/hgtloHe8SO

Great news: the Seminole County Vet Center we helped secure for our local veteran community now has a permanent home. Local servicemembers, veterans, & their families can now go to the Seminole County Health Department to get the care they have earned. Info below.  https://t.co/aGJJcYxJls
I’m incredibly proud that America continues to attract families in search of liberty, opportunity, and a better life. We are and will forever be a beacon of hope and freedom for the world. (1/3)

When Hurricane Maria hit, families like Karina’s left Puerto Rico in search of opportunity. I'm proud of the central FL community for welcoming our fellow Americans w/open arms. Working alongside allies like Father Rodriguez, I’ll always fight for equality for the PR community.  https://t.co/iQeUKUa0is

Gone, but not forgotten. As we approach another year since the tragedy at #Pulse, I'm once again displaying the names & faces of the 49 innocent lives cut short by hate. Each & every year they deserve to be remembered for the love they brought into this world. #OrlandoStrong  https://t.co/n5Mo7uhxc9

I'm devastated to hear of the passing of John Ensslin, a veteran of journalism, who has humbly covered Colorado for many years.   My prayers are with his wife, Denise, his friends and the entire @colo_politics community.

Two shootings in 24 hours. Over 29 dead.   We simply cannot wait any longer for meaningfully action to end this epidemic.   The Senate MUST step up to pass the common-sense reforms we passed in the House and take the first step to address the gun violence crisis.
This is a heartbreaking day for America. As we wait to learn more, we must all unite to speak against violence spurred by hate.

My sincerest thank you to the law enforcement officers, first responders, and community members who have come to the aid of the victims and families in El Paso and Dayton. I fully support the investigations being conducted at the local, state, and federal levels.
This is a heartbreaking day for America. As we wait to learn more, we must all unite to speak against violence spurred by hate.
Introducing an additional apex predator to an area that is populated by families and livestock is extremely concerning, but I am glad @Interior is seeking real, local public comments on this issue.

I spoke on the House floor to remember Rosenda Strong, an Umatilla woman whose remains were finally found on the Yakama Nation reservation. Congress must act to address the #MMIW crisis to deliver justice to victims like Rosenda and so many others.  https://t.co/JsQ8D6sU7m
Praying for the two ATF Special Agents who were injured as they worked to protect #WA04 communities from this dangerous drug operation. Thank you for your bravery!

It’s heartbreaking to hear of the attacks at the ICE detention center in Tacoma. I recently visited this facility and am praying for those affected. This type of violence should never be accepted or tolerated. Thank you to Tacoma PD for your quick response and bravery.

Proud to be an original cosponsor of HR1044 which will help address the backlog of employment-based immigrant visas for highly-skilled and highly-educated professionals that contribute to US communities and economies.

SAVE THE DATE: I am hosting a Central WA Health & Safety Fair on July 27 in Yakima. All individuals and families are invited to learn about personal, home, outdoor, and online health and safety. More details:  https://t.co/wBxsbxdlQS  https://t.co/yEdhGLP7W4
The families, communities, law enforcement, and advocates of #WA04 and Yakama Nation have a unique story to tell as we work to deliver justice to #MMIW in the U.S.  https://t.co/dcSRXma1Ha

Community health centers play an important role in ensuring there’s access to healthcare for all. That’s why, this week, we’re celebrating the centers that provide high-quality care for South Jersey families.  #NationalHealthCentersWeek #SouthJersey #ProtectOurCare  https://t.co/XWPlWznhvs

I wish this wasn’t necessary — @MomsDemand members write sympathy cards to the family members of victims in El Paso & Dayton.  Hey @HouseGOP & @SenateGOP — let’s write sensible laws instead of sympathy letters!  #EnoughIsEnough #DoSomething #HR8 #ElPasoStrong #DaytonStrong  https://t.co/qsV2PDkIab

Strong police-community relationships are crucial & it’s always a pleasure to celebrate successes at @GloTwp’s #NationalNightOut.  Everyone benefits when law enforcement engages consistently with leaders, organizations & families in our neighborhoods.  https://t.co/gBKAfA3u0c
This is tragic & insane. We must act to save lives.  #HR8 - the Bipartisan Background Checks Act - is waiting on Sen. McConnell’s desk. #EnoughIsEnough

Today, I voted to support our 9/11 heroes.   Our first responders, of course, deserve to have the September 11th Victim Compensation Fund there to help them & their families for as long as they need it. #Renew911VCF  https://t.co/fz0b8uHyWm

We must protect the hard-earned retirement security of hundreds of thousands of working families & retirees across the country.  After the financial collapse, Congress acted to take care of Wall St. If you can save the banks, you can save the people. #ButchLewisAct #ForThePeople  https://t.co/tiEALOYCQ2
More proof that now is the time for our country to follow my home state’s lead & give working families a fair shot.  #RaiseTheWage #FightFor15  https://t.co/ijnA3B3NGn @fightfor15
Bittersweet day in North Camden — as we mourn the tragic loss of Curtis Jenkins III & open a new gym to provide recreation opportunities for children.  @CityOfCamdenGov  https://t.co/D28GGZQpfm

📺 WATCH LIVE ➡️  https://t.co/wgYrlyVfs1   Today, the minimum wage in NJ goes up to $10 an hour. It’s part of a plan to get to $15 that offers predictability for employers & fairness for working families.   In DC, we need to #RaiseTheWage!

With more rain on the way, I’ve been coordinating efforts with @RepAndyKimNJ, @CongressmanJVD & all of our area mayors to ensure we’re best serving #SouthJersey’s families, homeowners, commuters & first responders.  #severeweather #flooding @cpsj @burlcotimes @njdotcom (3/3)

column14: Today's the 3rd anniversary of the #Pulse Nightclub shooting. As we remember the 49 people who lost their lives, we must push for a world without hate-fueled violence & with action to #EndGunViolence.  #PrideMonth  #LoveIsLove #EnoughIsEnough  https://t.co/vKVKcyKyu6
ICYMI - We took an important first step in protecting the hard-earned retirement security of hundreds of thousands of working families & retirees across the country.  https://t.co/2SFKV1Kd80
I grieve for the families and communities who lost loved ones in California, Texas, and Ohio.  We need to call out these acts for what they are: Terrorism.

I fully support resuming federal executions.   Dylann Roof is on death row for racially targeting and murdering 9 churchgoers in Charleston. I have yet to hear a compelling reason why any other sentence would do. #DeathPenality #Justice #MotherEmanuel    https://t.co/LpTmfDKhWD

@RepChipRoy is exactly right.  It's an open secret on the Hill who really calls the shots for @HouseDemocrats. The "Squad" is in power and they are not afraid to show it: Impeachment, Green New Deal, Open Borders, calling moderate Dems racist..  @SpeakerPelosi has lost control.
Warms my heart. What an incredible young man. Congratulations @igotgame_12 on being picked #2 in #NBADraft and congratulations @memgrizz for picking one of Dalzell, SC's incredible talents.

Reports of a South Carolina State Trooper shot & injured in York County this evening.  Right now, please take a moment to lift him up in prayer. Along with every single man and woman who walks the thin blue line.
🚨UPDATE: Stable Homes Stable Schools “13 families have been housed and six have been approved for rental housing units and are waiting to sign a lease”  https://t.co/YTuomeEEN0

States that are paying workers $15/hour have seen an increase in job growth and consumer spending.   Don’t believe those who profit from low wages! Increasing the minimum wage will help small businesses and families.   https://t.co/oRrmDeSGHa
I joined @News12NJ to talk about legislation to #endgunviolence, my work to combat #climatechange, and why New Jersey needs a strong flood insurance program.  https://t.co/pUy5qlI24u
We’re lucky to live in a state like New Jersey that takes gun violence prevention seriously, but we need comprehensive federal legislation to #endgunviolence.  https://t.co/PMyR2rFSwq

Two mass shootings in 24 hours is beyond unacceptable. This won’t stop until the Senate takes up comprehensive gun control legislation and sends it to the president’s desk for a signature. #EndGunViolence

This is absolutely shameful. Trump's plan to kick Americans off of #SNAP and prevent hundreds of thousands of children from receiving school meals is heartless and must be stopped. No child in America should go hungry.  https://t.co/RrKSdRZ7JF

Heartbroken for the families of the victims in Gilroy, CA. Another day of senseless violence in America because of @senatemajldr's unwillingness to relinquish his party from the @NRA’s stranglehold. It’s time for the Senate to pass H.R. 8 and commonsense gun safety legislation.
Happy Independence Day! I hope you have an enjoyable holiday with your families celebrating our great nation. I'm thankful to be an American every day. #IndependenceDay2019  https://t.co/T9Sqx1vogx
Thank you to the MOAA for the work you do advocating for service members and military families.

There is nothing more important than safeguarding the health and well-being of our communities and families. We owe it to them to roll up our sleeves and work in a bipartisan manner to keep people safe by taking action against toxic PFAS compounds.   https://t.co/pCvdgTXkd3
In 2018 domestic extremists killed 50 people in the US  49 homicides were by right-wing extremists  0 homicides were by left-wing extremists  Source:  https://t.co/TykGzJRumf

I voted for a bill that passed the House to finally study how to stop gun violence in this country.  Hopefully, the Senate and President will pass it, so we can put an end to the tragic American epidemic of gun violence.  #Enoughisenough

My heartfelt condolences to the family, friends and many, many fans of Toni Morrison.  The beloved author and first African American woman to win the Nobel Prize passed away today at 88.  She is an inspiration to our entire community and will be missed.

WH acting COS Mick Mulvaney said Trump's words aren't responsible for the mass shootings this weekend.  Yet, Trump has attacked immigrants and said there are "good people" in the white supremacy movement.  Here's whats come from his statements.        https://t.co/h2EUghX7pB

My condolences and prayers to the people of El Paso & Dayton.  I'm horrified and angry that Trump & Senate refuse to stop this anger, hate and violence. But I’m not going to give up the fight… EVER... until ALL Americans are safe!  #enoughisenough #endgunviolence

Two days ago, I called for the resignation of Alexander Acosta as Labor Secretary. Today, I want to thank him for his service and resignation today.  His "sweetheart deal" to convicted sex abuser Jeffrey Epstein showed he lacked the conviction needed to support victims of abuse,

Republicans make perfectly clear what GOP control of Washington means for families: soaring costs, worse coverage & the end of protections for people w/ pre-existing conditions. @HouseDemocrats are fighting relentlessly to stop this health care sabotage.  https://t.co/S1ZYTPuon1

In less than 24 hours, another American community has been devastated by the tragedy of gun violence, this time in Dayton, Ohio. The hearts of all Americans break for the families & friends of those injured & murdered in this act of terror. #EnoughIsEnough
Read my full statement following today’s horrific shooting in El Paso here:  https://t.co/WcL5Ze3MeB  https://t.co/bBND20PZ6A

We are closely monitoring the situation in El Paso. While we are grateful for heroic first responders, our hearts ache for the families of those who were killed & the injured. Action must be taken to finally #EndGunViolence.

Ever since they were signed into law 54 years ago, Medicare & Medicaid have stood as a promise to seniors & working families. House Democrats are committed to protecting these pillars of fairness, justice & health security for generations to come.  https://t.co/pmWzCUV6I0  https://t.co/xkgMQnD63V
Today represents a hard-fought victory for the heroes of 9/11 and their families. #Renew911VCF  https://t.co/QScF9yrlls  https://t.co/8HUAFyXnNQ

Our thoughts are with the families of those lost last night in Gilroy, CA, as well as the survivors facing a tough road ahead. But thoughts are not enough — action must be taken to #EndGunViolence. Every day the Senate refuses to act is a stain on the conscience of our nation.

Reports that the Trump Administration is separating families on the basis of HIV status are outrageous. @DHSgov must clarify that this shameful policy will end immediately. #FamiliesBelongTogether  https://t.co/EpJN4qaifN

My message to the @SenateGOP is simple: #DoSomething. It’s been 160 days since I cast my vote for the Bipartisan Background Checks Act – yet @SenateMajLdr McConnell has refused to bring this life-saving legislation to a vote. How much longer should families have to wait?  https://t.co/HqoEUfm7PP

Hardworking folks in the middle are getting squeezed at every turn. From crushing student loan debt to rising housing costs yet stagnant pay. This situation is unsustainable and we need to focus on ways to provide more opportunity for middle class families  https://t.co/2FX7MfL7pW

The racism, hatred & violence must stop. It starts w/inclusive, non-discriminatory rhetoric & serious reforms to our gun laws. The ppl of CO know this type of devastation & heartbreak too well & I will continue to do everything I can to ensure no community experiences it again.

The news of the #ElPasoShooting is devastating. No family, no community deserves this type of violence and heartbreak. Thank you to the first responders and my deepest condolences to the victims, their families and the entire El Paso community. #EnoughIsEnough #ElPasoStrong

Joined @OfficialSDMAC to share our work to combat the Tijuana sewage spill, provide for servicemembers and military families, and fund important construction projects that strengthen San Diego's role in the national defense and boost our local economy.  https://t.co/0uIv8bQAOy

On #PurpleHeartDay, we salute the men and women killed or wounded in combat. Their bravery earned them the oldest military decoration in the armed forces and our eternal gratitude. Thank you for your service and sacrifice.  https://t.co/TmBejN21xV
“The only variable that can explain the high rate of mass shootings in America is its astronomical number of guns.”  It’s not complicated.   https://t.co/2701yg18RM
.@realdonaldtrump: This is on you. Your hate speech is motivating murder. Enough.
Another angry young man with a weapon of war murders innocent people.  @senatemajldr: Don’t you dare offer your 'thoughts and prayers' if they aren't followed by action. #HonorWithAction

Devastating news out of El Paso. We are grateful to the first responders on the scene. Our hearts are with the families of the victims and those injured.   This can’t be our new normal. The House took action. @senatemajldr: How can you continue to look the other way? #NotOneMore

Tariffs are taxes paid by U.S. businesses, workers, and families. Escalating tensions with China is not the way to get them to the negotiating table. China will almost certainly retaliate, hurting the U.S. economy and consumers even more.   https://t.co/SEJLjfUhyX

The Women's Health Protection Act safeguards health care services that are critical to the economic and social well-being of women and families. I'm one of over 200 cosponsors in the House because we must protect access to reproductive care. #ActForWomen

This week, our community lost a courageous firefighter: Yaroslav Katkov. My deepest condolences go out to Yaroslav's family and the @CAL_FIRE San Diego unit. We are forever grateful for his service.  https://t.co/x2pQj5DuBH

Our hearts are with the Gilroy community during this tragic time. No one should live in fear of going to festivals or anywhere in America. This senseless violence must end.  No more excuses. The Senate must act. #GilroyStrong #NotOneMore  https://t.co/1Z348vXYga

San Diego veterans: We're looking for feedback on the new VA MISSION Act Community Care standards, which went into effect last month. Share your thoughts here >> https://t.co/PdyXRoGLm9  https://t.co/ik4VmtOCgj

We welcomed @danielsparents to D.C. this week. We passed the Daniel Somers Network of Support Act to engage families about servicemembers' experiences, potentially preventing isolation and suicide. Now we want to expand this concept to the VA for veterans and their families.  https://t.co/vjKq2JmeuY

Yesterday, the House passed the #ButchLewisAct to protect thousands of Americans who were at risk of losing the retirement savings they’ve earned over decades of work through no fault of their own. The Senate must do the same to help these families and save taxpayer dollars.  https://t.co/YwunfefNdB

Thank you @SenatorSinema for championing The Daniel Somers Network of Support Act in the Senate to better support our servicemembers and ensure fewer families have to endure a loss as the Somers did.   You're right: It's exactly the kind of work that matters.
An increase to the federal minimum wage is overdue to increase economic opportunity for American families, which is why I helped pass the #RaiseTheWageAct today.   https://t.co/Vs6w94Fnrv
Annalise and I were welcomed with soulful music, warm smiles and delicious food by these extraordinary Minnesotans at Igbo Fest in @BrooklynPark. My heart is so full.  https://t.co/LMAu9qxo0S

Minnesota farmers told me that they're not interested in handouts. Our hardworking ag families want access to markets. They're worried that disappearing markets as a result of ongoing, reactionary trade wars will devastate their way of life.  https://t.co/IB6BnU6jrT
I’m sick of crying. I’m sick of tweeting. I’m sick of worrying about my children. These Minnesotans and I will honor the victims of gun violence with action.  https://t.co/DTDpNO79tQ

Thinking tonight of the Orange County families and first responders coping with the aftermath of this attack. My heart is with them.  We don’t yet know the motives of this vicious attack, but I will be monitoring information from law enforcement closely.  https://t.co/O6D0wbBC1Z

I am heartened that @usedgov made the right decision & chose to maintain federal aid for 80,000 students in CA. Last week, I led 18 of my colleagues calling on @BetsyDeVosED not to take aid away from our students.  https://t.co/4bkQfnU4Fd
Gun violence is so common in the United States that 3 survivors of the #Gilroy shooting also survived the 2017 shooting in Las Vegas.  https://t.co/YcXpgtqwjd
But let’s be clear: these two incidents weren’t even the only two mass shootings in the past 7 days. See for yourself >>  https://t.co/M1GoD25QDI
Not even one week later, another tragic mass shooting. I am thinking of our fellow Americans in #ElPaso.

Why are 100 Americans killed by guns every day?  Hint: It’s not mental health. It’s not video games. It's guns.     We have a moral responsibility to take action NOW.   I’ve called for change & for @realDonaldTrump, @senatemajldr, & @housegop, to #EndGunViolence. Here's proof:

#Dayton is now on a list no community wants to be: places with a deadly mass shooting. Our hearts are with the victims & loved ones as they begin to pick up the pieces.  Two mass shootings in less than 24 hours. We must act to end gun violence in every community.  #NotOneMore

Thinking of the victims, their families, first responders and the entire El Paso community.   Mass shootings have become all too common in the United States - and so has inaction. Enough is enough. #EndGunViolence

President Trump has used his presidency to stoke fear in immigrant communities. In El Paso, there are reports that there were individuals who didn't seek treatment after the shooting out of fear of deportation. The President's words have consequences.  https://t.co/kSwr2Dz8dK

Last week, I got to visit Plymouth Place Seniors Center and speak to a room full of my senior constituents. It's always great to hear their thoughts and concerns for our district.  https://t.co/Qkcp53aa6g

It is long past time for @realDonaldTrump to acknowledge the impact of his racist attacks on immigrant communities. Mr. President, 22 people are dead. You owe their friends and families more than empty gestures.   https://t.co/MJPpH9qJep

We owe the American people more than "thoughts and prayers" in response to the gun violence epidemic in our country. Earlier this year, I introduced a bill to establish an alert system when someone prohibited from purchasing a firearm attempts to do so.  https://t.co/czFydeb8tS

.@RepSpeier is right. Too many perpetrators have a history of abusing women. We owe it to survivors mass shootings & dmoestic violence to understand the link between this violence. That's why I introduced a bill to do exactly that:  https://t.co/aZLBUWRD6i  https://t.co/XrRr5pbtQI

My deepest condolences to the family, friends, and fellow officers of Officer Calvin Hall, a hero whose commitment to serving and protecting his community didn’t end when he was off-duty. He will be remembered for his selfless service and sacrifice.

Democrats want to destroy everything we achieved in the last 2 years with their minimum wage hike, which even the non-partisan @USCBO says will kill nearly 4 million American jobs and reduce household incomes for American families by $8.7 billion. (2/3)

At a complete loss for words. Another mass shooting, this time in Dayton.   Praying for everyone who was affected by these two tragedies.  This is heartbreaking. And it's infuriating, because our leaders in the White House and Senate clearly lack the courage to end this crisis.
My heart breaks for the victims of yet another mass shooting. I’m praying for all of El Paso today.  This cannot continue. We cannot let this become normal.

This was such a wonderful event! On behalf of #NY04, I want to thank @EnesKanter and the great folks at Island Garden for hosting these kids and their families.  What an incredible way to give back!  https://t.co/PmFez8muET

Finally, 9/11 first responders and families will have the support and peace of mind they deserve. So grateful to everyone who made this possible, especially the brave men and women of the FDNY and NYPD, who fought harder and sacrificed more than anyone.  https://t.co/eyoTGa2Gst

What happened in El Paso today has got to stop. Mass shootings should have no place in American society. I send my strength and condolences to all of the families and friends connected to the innocent lives that were lost.
I’d like to wish you and your families a happy and safe Fourth of July celebration today! #IndependenceDay

My heart broke this weekend when I heard about the tragedies in El Paso and Dayton.  I condemn the white nationalism of the shooter as a vile and disgusting ideology that has no place in America.  We should all stand with one voice against such hatred.

The opioid epidemic has hurt too many families across the country and in #VA05.  I’ve been working with @RepDavidTrone and the Bipartisan Freshman Working Group on Addiction to address this crisis.  (1/2)

I was honored to speak to @NFED_ORG families visiting Capitol Hill this morning and talk about the Ensuring Lasting Smiles Act, a bill I am sponsoring to help children born with congenital anomalies get the care they need.

ICYMI, last night I spoke on the House floor about my amendment to the National Defense Authorization Act.  The amendment directs the Secretary of Defense to develop a plan for a pilot program to train skilled technicians for placement in the defense industrial base. #Va05  https://t.co/suB0Ur96Pe
Great to have the Cole families from Auburn at our #MorningsWithMike event today!  Thanks for coming! #AL03  https://t.co/8p7y1s0EaP
Thanks to these families from Auburn for coming to #MorningsWithMike! #AL03  https://t.co/PpmFljaqk6

We continue to mourn the loss of precious lives in El Paso, TX, & Dayton, OH. Senseless tragedies of this kind are incredibly heartbreaking & the cowards who commit these crimes must be brought to justice. My prayers are with the victims & first responders in these communities.

Thank you to this great group for meeting today to discuss distillers’ legislative concerns. I always appreciate folks from #TN6 making the trip to Washington, DC to share their thoughts.  https://t.co/eniSfw5nHd

Hey @senatemajldr, here's a refresher on the democratic process.   A majority of Americans support common-sense gun control legislation, like H.R. 8, which @HouseDemocrats and @HouseGOP passed.   Now it's YOUR turn to call a vote in the Senate.  https://t.co/eP1KVAocdo
I’m just devastated for Encinitas. My heart goes out to the families of the victims and the community.

It was an honor to speak at the Korean Church Coalition Shout for Human Rights in North Korea rally. When discussing the Korean Conflict, we need to focus on the human face of the Korean Peninsula; the thousands of families who have been separated for decades.  https://t.co/2ohtE6oAMu

Today, our delegation is in Honduras. We had a briefing from the U.S. Embassy, visited a bazaar, and met with Foreign Minister. I was also humbled to meet the mother of Berta Cáceres, who was murdered for her work to protect human rights, indigenous lands, and the environment.  https://t.co/3KHKXzoksw

I have introduced the Child Trafficking Victims Protection and Welfare Act to help us keep migrant children safe, care for trafficking victims, and prohibit family separation at America’s border. We cannot rest until every child is safe, healthy, and free from fear.

Today, our congressional delegation visited Guatemala’s Tour De Amour shelter, which aids returning migrant children. Tragically, many of these children have been victims of sexual violence and trafficking.  My heart broke for these kids – we must do all we can to help them.  https://t.co/RVXE542oEI

I’m outraged that these kids faced the nightmare of living without their parents after the Trump Admin took their mothers and fathers away. America MUST do better than this. As DHS @AppropsDems Chair, I'll keep fighting for humane immigration policies that keep families together.

I had a wonderful visit to the fast-growing @ViaCareLA to celebrate #HealthCenterWeek. I thanked staff for their work in the community, and I spoke to patients and families about their concerns, including how to lower the costs of healthcare and prescription drugs #ForThePeople  https://t.co/fcFLNdu2fx

As a mother and grandmother, I have been heartbroken by the deaths of migrant children in our government's custody. We cannot allow @CBPgov to keep holding children and families in overcrowded and life-threatening conditions.

Every single migrant in our government’s care must be kept safe & treated humanely. As DHS @AppropsDems Chairwoman, I am fighting to ensure @CBPgov has the policies & resources it needs to meet this crucial goal, and to address public health concerns before they lead to tragedy.

In May, Trump grinned when someone suggested shooting immigrants. His tweets are full of racist bile. His statements encourage & empower white nationalism & white supremacy. He must end his bigoted rhetoric & demand the Senate pass @HouseDemocrats’ bills to help #EndGunViolence.

@indivisible410 @AppropsDems You’re right. This was a missed opportunity. My intent was to ask @ICEgov why they are focusing on families instead of bad guys. I am equally horrified by the separation of families, the raids and the inhumane treatment of those in government care, but clearly I missed the mark.

Two massacres in 24 hours. My heart goes out to the loved ones of the victims and first responders of #ElPasoShooting + #daytonshooting. Words can’t express my sadness and utter frustration and are useless anyway. We must #dosomething.

@NorahODonnell @weijia With all due respect to my friends in the press, the President does not deserve a pat on the back for doing the bare minimum. Condemning racism should be the floor, not the bar.   The American people want action—not halfhearted tweets and poorly recited teleprompter speeches.

@CDCgov @RepChrisSmith @UofNorthFlorida @RepMaloney @NormaJTorres 8/ VA's current policy does not provide for the children of homeless vets. To fix this, I cosponsored @RepBrownley's Homeless Veteran Families Act, which ensures their families are not overlooked. More on the local fight against veteran homelessness below.  https://t.co/SrS5E4xVN5

column14: My heart breaks for the victims of yesterday’s senseless shootings. We as a nation must stand against violence & hatred in all its forms. I pray for the communities of El Paso and Dayton during this trying time, especially for those lost and their families. May they find peace.

Great analysis by the Washington Post on the damage a federally mandated $15 minimum wage would inflict on “society’s most vulnerable.” I hope Democrats reconsider this job-killing proposal and instead work with @HouseGOP to help all workers get ahead.  https://t.co/jqt5JRcYWO

June marked the 11th straight month that year-over-year wage gains were over 3%. The best part? Wages are rising for those who need it most. In fact, lower income families are seeing DOUBLE the wage growth of the top half of earners.  https://t.co/K8zY4wgsV1
Wishing a safe deployment to Jacksonville's own 125th Fighter Wing. May God Bless our brave service members and their families.

It's heart-wrenching. This is the 31st baby or toddler who has suffered a terrible hot car death this year.  @auto_alliance, how many more children have to die before you support bipartisan, common-sense legislation to save these lives? #PasstheHOTCARSAct  https://t.co/hQl01wpvL0

The El Paso shooting marked one of the deadliest attacks on the Latinx community in US history. And it has left many shaken up.   Judith is demanding change. Listen to her message. #CaravanForChange  https://t.co/TlnJBIF52J
This is why we fight. For Jordan. For Andre. For their family. And for the countless families who have lost loved ones to senseless acts of gun violence.

I’m heartbroken. I’m angry. This is the second mass shooting in the U.S. in less than 24 hours.   My prayers go out to Dayton and those affected. And I’m thankful to the First Responders on the scene.  We need gun reform. The House did its job. The Senate needs to do theirs.
Absolutely devastated. My heart breaks for the El Paso community.   We cannot allow this to be the norm. We need action to #EndGunViolence.

Two more precious babies are dead and the automobile industry @auto_alliance continues to drag its feet on improved safety features that would have prevented this tragedy. How many more children need to die? The sooner we pass the HOT CARS Act the more kids we can save.

6 years old. My heart breaks for the Romero family, all those affected by this tragedy and the entire Gilroy community. This cannot be the norm of our country. We need change, and it starts by passing comprehensive gun reform. #EnoughIsEnough

As a member of the Subcomittee on Military Construction, the Administration is stealing funds from our military servicemembers and their families. We need comprehensive immigration reform, not an ineffective, wasteful Trump vanity project.

Trump says he's working to lower drug prices, but yet he's pushing for a trade deal that's a giveaway to Big Pharma. In its current form, the #USMCA locks in high prices and harms hard-working families trying to afford life-saving medication. #FixUSMCA  https://t.co/VII9xk4NNV

Hard-working families have gone without an increase in the federal minimum wage for more than a decade. Too many Americans are working multiple jobs to make ends meet, 40% cannot withstand a $400 emergency & nearly 80% are living paycheck to paycheck.  https://t.co/6tGZ2g8Uxg
This is heartbreaking. How many more, @auto_alliance? We need to pass the HOT CARS Act.   https://t.co/CMyAnH3yz0

Migrant families and children are seeking asylum to escape violence and persecution. This backward policy to end asylum protections will only put them more in danger. We do not turn our back on those that need help.
We need to get children out of these facilities immediately and reunite those separated with their families. They deserve better, and we must all demand better from the United States of America.

One year ago, I spoke out against Trump's family separation policy on the House Floor. Today, we're seeing reports & pictures of how families, children & babies are being grossly mistreated in the detention centers. When will we decide we've seen enough?  https://t.co/peq8tELs7O

A huge victory for women & families across Ohio. The government has no place in the decisions made between a woman & her doctor. I don't care how many times that needs to be said, but I'll keep saying it until Republicans stop pushing these backward, unconstitutional bills.

We deserve commonsense gun control measures that keep our communities safe and prevent tragedies like El Paso and Dayton from happening. H.R. 1236, the Extreme Risk Protection Order Act, would allow families or law enforcement to ask for a gun violence prevention order from a court. The order would temporarily prohibit an individual who poses a threat to themselves or others from obtaining a firearm.

Ethan’s Law, would make it a crime for a firearm to be left unsecured if there’s a reasonable expectation that a child could gain access to it. This law seeks to prevent the horrific accidental shootings that can happen when a child gets hold of an unsecured gun.

H.R. 2585, the Resources for Victims of Gun Violence Act, would create a program to help the victims of gun violence with a wide range of personal needs that are often left unaddressed in the aftermath of gun violence.

Thank you to Fred and Maria Wright, parents of Jerald Arthur Wright, an angel we lost at #Pulse, for sharing your thoughts on #PulseNationalMemorial. I agree this must continue to be an “informative, inclusive, and open” process. #OrlandoStrong  https://t.co/Tzo6a9gEnK

We were just a few votes shy of passing #HR549 Venezuela TPS today. We're deeply disappointed over apathy shown towards struggling Venezuelans. We stand firm in this fight and will push for another vote this week! Maduro is murdering Venezuelans, we cannot send thousands back

I'm deeply saddened to hear of the passing of Councilman Ray Goodgame of Clermont. He was an outstanding leader in his community, and he will be deeply missed. My thoughts and prayers are with his family during this difficult time.

Last night we authorized appropriations for FY20 intel & related activities. Today we'll vote on some real bad legislation that wants to double the min wage and reverse most of the gains our economy has had the past 2 yrs. My thoughts can be found here:  https://t.co/wbjjhLDlmm

Glad to vote yes on H.R. 748 Middle Class Health Benefits Tax Repeal Act of 2019 to permanently repeal the 40% tax-hike on “high-cost” health benefits, known as the Obamacare Cadillac Tax. Big win for families and small businesses.
I'm currently sitting in a T&I Aviation Subcommittee Hearing on “State of Aviation Safety" and hearing from NTSB, a family tragically affected by the 737 Max, and others.  https://t.co/b04FVHLoGl

@POTUS @RepCummings @OversightDems @IlhanMN @RepAOC @RashidaTlaib @AyannaPressley @RepMalinowski @HouseDemocrats @HouseGOP “@POTUS’ plan to target immigrant families in his racist roundup WON'T fix our immigration challenges.
