column14: Sick to my stomach by the trauma & devastation suffered by so many in Gilroy. We will mourn the loss of 6-year-old Stephen Romero & the two others killed & not yet publicly ID’ed. My heart goes out to the 12 hurt, including Stephen’s mom and grandma. This loss cannot be in vain.

At a time when the challenges we face seem to divide our nation rather than being us together, I was heartened to be joined by 2x Academy Award winning actor Mahershala Ali, survivors Abdul Shakoor & Jewher Ilhan, & foreign & US officials for a discussion on religious tolerance.  https://t.co/KWUPvRRfsn

I was heartbroken to hear about yet another mass shooting – this time in #Gilroy. My heart is with the victims & survivors of this heinous act.   We CANNOT stand by & let this happen over & over again. The Senate MUST consider our commonsense gun safety bills. #EndGunViolence
My thoughts on Robert Mueller’s testimony today:  https://t.co/41VmcPsAEl #MI11

Big news! Last night, the House passed 2 of my bipartisan bills to strengthen advanced manufacturing & encourage young children - especially girls - to pursue STEM opportunities. Both bills are part of my vision for a strong, inclusive economy that empowers middle class families.

The American Manufacturing Leadership Act passed the house today!! Manufacturing is the economic heart of #MI11 and so much of America, and I’m so proud to have introduced this bipartisan legislation to support and strengthen our fantastic manufacturing economy.  https://t.co/xtIDRy3zpL

The irony of this bill? It hurts the very people it’s claiming to help. While some may have a higher wage, employers will not be able to afford to hire as many people—costing millions their jobs & putting financial strain on families across America. I’m proud to have voted no.

The responders, survivors, and families affected by 9/11 can be assured: our nation has their back, just as they have always had ours. I am pleased that the September 11th Victim Compensation Fund, that I cosponsored, passed the Senate today and is headed to the President’s desk.  https://t.co/JGe8xjL1GT

For 54 years, thousands of seniors and families have relied on #Medicare & #Medicaid to provide lifesaving healthcare. We will not let the Republicans in Congress succeed in gutting these programs, which serve as a vital lifeline for so many.
If you, or anyone you know, was affected by the tragic shooting at the #GilroyGarlicFestival please check out these community resources. Know that my office is here to help in any capacity we can.

These 2 moms worked to make Chicago’s South Side safer through Mother’s Against Senseless Killings (MASK). I’ve had the privilege of working with the group’s leader, @TamarManasseh. I grieve with their families and know their work will inspire new hands and hearts to help out.
This WILL NOT be America’s normal. I refuse and will fight it with everything I have. And I know you will, too. #gilroyshooting  https://t.co/07i5BZNWuf
My heart breaks for all of our Bay Area neighbors who attended the #GilroyGarlicFestival. We need gun reform and we need it now. #EnoughIsEnough

Today we heard from Director Mueller about Trump associates who were caught lying to investigators. I asked why it's so important that witnesses tell the truth. His response? "Because the testimony of the witnesses goes to the heart of just about any criminal case you have."  https://t.co/nqoPeftzvS
I’m done listening to lectures about being un-American from the party whose Kentucky senator just blocked a bill to save 9/11 victims.
I spoke with @TKopan from @sfchronicle about this tragedy and what action must be taken by the Senate immediately.  https://t.co/Wv1bCcvbS4

Leader McConnell needs to do his job. 8,443 people have died this year due to gun violence. 16,697 have been injured. 373 of those killed and injured were children. Sen. McConnell is living up to his nickname. We demand Senate action on gun violence.
In just 7 months, our country has experienced nearly 250 mass shootings. Last night, Gilroy was sadly added to that list.
Today we pause and remember those lives lost and those lives forever changed in the shooting in Aurora seven years ago. We must continue our fight to #EndGunViolence in their honor.

Today Jan and I are mourning the passing of Don Mossi, former World Series pitcher. Proud of my cousin and his great baseball career. Our thoughts are with his loved ones and all who celebrated his time on the field.

Flame Mitigation Devices will prevent tragic fire accidents and help save lives. That’s why I am proud to that announce my bipartisan bill to address this problem and establish a standard for fuel container safety has cleared committee and is headed to the floor for a vote.

My heart breaks for Gilroy. As we thank the first responders on the scene who likely prevented further injuries and loss of life, we must remember that we aren't powerless in the face of the gun violence epidemic. This is a public health crisis and we must treat it as such.

Today #TeamTitus attended the Minority Mental Health Forum hosted by @naacplv to hear from industry experts about the importance of balanced mental health in our families and our communities.  https://t.co/a0xcBShc5Z

Happy birthday Medicare & Medicaid! 54 years later, these life-saving cornerstones of America's safety net continue to work #ForThePeople. Millions of America's seniors, middle class & working families, and more have had access to healthcare thanks to these programs!
To his family, friends and his many supporters in Schenectady County and beyond, I offer my humble and heartfelt condolences for what is truly a great loss.

A great public servant of our New York Capital Region, former Schenectady County Legislator Jim Buhrmaster, passed away this week. I wrote some of my thoughts about Jim at the time and would like to share a small selection.  https://t.co/wYPAfxDHiG

A heartbreaking story of a young man, murdered simply because he was in a gang territory getting a bite to eat with friends. He is not just a police officer, he was a young man with a bright future who chose to walk away from a fight. 😢🙏🏼 #StopTheViolence

This week @HouseDemocrats advanced legislation to prevent more than 5K of my constituents in #CA35 from losing their retirement savings. We're standing up & fighting for the benefits millions of American families have planned for & earned over decades of hard work. #ButchLewisAct  https://t.co/2a9LkzB9hq
Hey @realDonaldTrump, how about a travel ban for the corrupt elected officials instead? Don't punish innocent families.

We weren't all born w/ a silver spoon in our mouths like @realDonaldTrump. @USDA's cruel SNAP restrictions put 3 million Americans at risk of going hungry—like in this PA school district where poor families are threatened w/ separation because they can't afford school lunches.

NM families and tribes continue to pay the price for the nuclear research advanced during the Cold War era. That's why @RepDebHaaland @repbenraylujan & I have introduced legislation to compensate families affected by radiation exposure. #RECA2019  More:  https://t.co/q7JBR6SKYs

I am sending my deepest condolences to the people of Gilroy. Among the victims was a six year-old boy.  This is outrageous and it cannot continue. Children and families deserve to feel safe in their communities, free of the constant threat of gun violence.  https://t.co/zhty2nxiKl

I pray for the victims, their families, and the people of Gilroy. Gun violence is an epidemic that impacts far too many communities across this great nation.   Enough is enough. This senseless violence must end - we need gun reform now.
.@realDonaldTrump and his failed immigration policies are responsible for keeping THOUSANDS of children from their families. This is tragic.  https://t.co/P2XG925tAS

Today we gathered to mourn the 18th cyclist lost in NYC this year.   This is not only tragic - it is unacceptable. Yes we are heartbroken, but we are also calling for change.  I hope to never attend another gathering like this again.  My thanks to @NYCCouncil38 for coordinating.  https://t.co/YUJgb9U81o

I've authored legislation to crackdown on the "iron pipeline" of guns flowing into our city from other states.   We need tangible proposals like this and greater investment in anti-violence programs.   Words, thoughts & prayers are not enough.

It is beyond heartbreaking that at an event meant to celebrate longtime residents of a BK community, we would see such senseless violence.    Right now, I'm mourning along with the rest of NYC but we also need meaningful action to address gun violence.   https://t.co/5IcrTrDh8R
My heart breaks for the countless families that have been torn apart by Boko Haram's #ReignOfTerror. #BringBackOurGirls  https://t.co/rh7mICEdzu

Today we're holding a second hearing on the Protecting the Right to Organize Act, just a few months after the first. This is a fight we can't give up on so that everyone can earn decent wages & be able to care for their families & themselves. @EdLaborCmte   https://t.co/igVxccPefV
Russia isn’t done attacking our democracy. #RetweetTheReport  https://t.co/uc4tas2E2a
Deeply saddened by the passing of my good friend Joe Maxey of Harrison. He will be sorely missed by all of us. My heartfelt prayers go out to Julie, Clay, and the entire family.

Today marks 25 years since the tragic #AMIA terror attack in Argentina. This bombing was one of the worst anti-Semitic attacks since WWII. It was humbling to pay my respects & lay a wreath at the memorial site this year. We will never forget those lost or let hate win. #AMIA25  https://t.co/zXDgjkETTz
RIP, Justice John Paul Stevens. A Navy veteran of WWII, he went on to serve on the Supreme Court for 35 years. He lived a life of public service, and I extend my deepest condolences to his family.

Congrats to @Starbucks on reaching their goal of hiring 25,000 veterans and military spouses. We owe our veterans and their families so much. Prioritizing the hiring of veterans and their spouses is a great way to continue to support them in communities across the country.

The opioid crisis has ravaged communities in Tennessee and taken a toll on so many families. I raised these concerns with @FBI Director Wray @senjudiciary yesterday and he commended @FBIKnoxville for the hard work they are doing to get opioids out of Tennessee homes.  https://t.co/6jotnCX7VW

Gun violence is at a 40-year high, but less funding is given for research than car crashes or any other leading cause of fatalities. It is not enough to talk about these tragedies & give thoughts/prayers. We have questions & we need answers. #ResearchSavesLives  https://t.co/6F9DVgvbba
We need a new trade agreement that works better for ranching families, farming families, for workers, for manufacturers. It’s time for Congress to pass #USMCAnow  https://t.co/45XLy4BXRz

Everyone who has been affected by this tragedy deserves answers & certainty that it will never happen again. Coast Guard & National Transportation Safety Board have had more than enough time to complete their investigations, issue recommendations & implement new safety measures
One year ago, 17 people lost their lives in the duck boat tragedy at Table Rock Lake. We remember the victims & pray for their families & loved ones.

We owe a debt of gratitude to the 9/11 first responders and their families for their courage and bravery in the face of unthinkable tragedy. Thanks to their tireless advocacy, the Senate just voted to #Renew911VCF. NJ heroes will finally get the support they deserve.

It’s deeply disturbing that AG Barr would overrule DOJ’s career prosecutors – who specialize in excessive use-of-force cases – in not filing charges related to the tragic death of Eric Garner.   The public should know the basis for this decision.  https://t.co/ulS0otFcig

It’s crucial that we’re protecting the rights of workers and union families as part of the labor enforcements in #USMCA. This deal must stand for American workers & strong labor rights for all workers  https://t.co/51bUaEH66Q

Since Medicare & Medicaid were signed into law by President Johnson 54 years ago, hundreds of millions of seniors, children, people living with disabilities & families have been able to access critical healthcare & have peace of mind – including hundreds of thousands of Nevadans.  https://t.co/TaodVBSwE4

The death penalty is a just response to the most heinous crimes. I commend the president & AG Barr for resuming executions to carry out sentences for five brutal murderers. Justice will soon be done for these criminals’ many victims.  https://t.co/iqjVTNSq5a
My statement on the death of Stone County Sheriff’s Deputy Sgt. Mike Stephen, who was killed in the line of duty today:  https://t.co/ZYVfiUhOhu
My prayers are with @senatorlsakson. Wishing him a fast recovery and looking forward to having him back on the Senate floor soon!  https://t.co/26hAvzook8

On the ground at the southern border are the dedicated, compassionate, & good-hearted men & women of @CBP. I'm grateful for their willingness to serve our nation in this way, & we need to make sure they have the support they need to address this crisis.  https://t.co/DekQWDpfP6  https://t.co/1j8MwvY0pw

As Americans, we should do everything in our power to repay our veterans & military families. It’s always great to see our nation’s heroes getting the opportunities and support they surely deserve.  https://t.co/ZBAC23c04b

With all due respect, this isn’t paid leave. It's another proposal that would force working families to borrow from their own futures. Americans deserve a real national paid leave program for the full range of caregiving needs. That’s the #FAMILYAct—the best plan to get behind.

From Brownsville, Brooklyn to Gilroy, CA, communities across the country were devastated by gun violence this weekend.   My heart breaks for the victims and their families—and it breaks because these are all too common.   We must do everything we can to end this national crisis.

The 9/11 VCF reauthorization bill became the law of the land today.    Now, 9/11 first responders, survivors, & their families can finally have some peace of mind as they fight illnesses linked to their sacrifice.   I'm so grateful to all who helped pass this bill. #Renew911VCF

This administration has no compassion.   Millions of Americans—working families, children, seniors—rely on SNAP to get enough to eat. Now, we must witness yet another cruel proposal that would literally take away their access to food.  https://t.co/nESf6GGGRD

The Senate finally lived up to the promise to “Never Forget” by passing the bill to #Renew911VCF, 97-2.   This day is long overdue. Now, our 9/11 heroes can finally exhale and go home to be with their families. I urge President Trump to immediately sign the bill into law.  https://t.co/XiNrIJ88W9

LIVE: Joining 9/11 first responders, survivors, and their families following Senate passage of the "Never Forget the Heroes: James Zadroga, Ray Pfeifer, and Luis Alvarez Permanent Authorization of the September 11th Victim Compensation Fund" Act.  https://t.co/gS3cfY9GYj
My deepest condolences go to Richard Driscoll’s family, the 200th firefighter we have lost. 200 of our bravest.   The Senate can honor their memory and pass the 9/11 VCF bill on Tuesday. #Renew911VCF

Last night, the 9/11 First Responder community lost another hero, all while Congress stalled for yet another day to pass the 9/11 Victim Compensation Fund Bill.    Do we need any more reason to act?    Sending my heartfelt condolences to the Nolan family and their loved ones.
The Steen, Olson & Saddoris families from Ankeny, Pleasant Hill & Eagle Grove  https://t.co/d1k6gfe52e
the Moerman, Pena & Gael families from Sioux Center, Iowa City & Dubuque  https://t.co/GTbARwB9YC

In the wake of this weekend's devastating shootings, it is important to remember the scars gun violence leaves on everyone.    Read Clai's story. The Westmoreland local still suffers 50 years after she nearly lost her life ➡   https://t.co/RHrTtlkUGJ

Granite Staters are my #MondayMotivation – in fact, they're my motivation every day of the week!   To find out about what initiatives I'm working on to support New Hampshire families, keep an eye out for Twitter updates 👀

On opposite sides of the country, two communities were the scenes of horrific gun violence. My heart is with the families of victims in Brooklyn, NY and Gilroy, CA — and all the first responders. How many times must this happen before we can all agree that Congress must act?

One of the top concerns I hear? Prescription drug costs.   Seniors & families shouldn't have to make agonizing financial decisions to afford vital medication. 💊💰  Today we passed major bipartisan legislation out of committee to help lower prescription drug costs.  Watch now ▶  https://t.co/oKL4p4oaBe

My thoughts are with the family of Dr. Ed Kois, one of the Manchester VA whistleblowers, who passed away in a car accident yesterday.    Dr. Kois was relentless in working to ensure that veterans receive the highest quality care, and I'm incredibly grateful for his efforts.

.@LittleLobbyists families are MY heroes. Just getting out the door is an accomplishment when you're a parent of a child with disabilities (or any parent) – but these families go above and beyond through their extraordinary advocacy. Thank you!

The #Apollo11 moon landing captured the hearts and minds of Americans. 50 years later, a @dartmouth professor reflects on how watching Neil Armstrong's first steps on the moon inspired his own @NASA mission years later ➡  https://t.co/vxcFNfC3cl

The opioid crisis has hurt far too many Granite State families. I’m deeply grateful for Jeanne and Jim Moser’s advocacy following the heartbreaking loss of their son Adam.    Read more about the Mosers and a new, common-sense law to help save lives ➡  https://t.co/x0nhJIe8QP

We lost a legend yesterday. My heart goes out to Pumpsie Green’s loved ones – he was an extraordinary athlete and the first black player on the @RedSox. Read more about his legacy here ➡  https://t.co/kcqcpNk8WZ

Bring your innovation and drive to New Hampshire. With no sales or income tax, a skilled workforce, and an incredible quality of life (including four beautiful seasons unlike Silicon Valley…), we make a great home for your startup.    Don't just take it from me 👇

Now, it's time for the Senate to do the same and pass my bill with @SenatorRounds to ensure millions of middle-class families that rely on employer-based health care aren't unfairly penalized by this onerous tax.  https://t.co/0WxYjyXCVQ

Children as young as infants and toddlers have been taken from their families. Migrant families and children are being held in overcrowded, prison-like facilities.   This is not how we should treat our fellow human beings.  https://t.co/rJNsbVBK0U

The Trump Administration gave a $1.5 trillion tax cut to the extremely wealthy and large corporations.   Now they want to pull the rug out from hardworking families who are already struggling in today’s economy.   They need to get their priorities straight. https://t.co/Crv7fvvCdE

I'm pleased the House voted to permanently repeal the Cadillac Tax and protect vital benefits for workers. Now it's time for the Senate to do the same to ensure millions of middle-class families who rely on employer-based health care aren't unfairly penalized by this onerous tax.
Welcome home to the @3rd_Infantry soldiers! The Rock of the Marne has held fast yet again, and we thank these soldiers and their families for their service. #ROTM @FORSCOM @USARMY @USAGStewartHAAF

The conversation about solutions to the border crisis often revolves around ways to help @CBP detain people. While we should care about conditions at @CBP facilities, we must remember @ICEgov has the primary job of detaining individuals and families who have crossed illegally.  https://t.co/ncluP3c1C6
@CBP We need to realize our laws are broken. The humanitarian crisis is not only breaking our hearts for what's occurring at the border, but it's also become a critical issue we must solve in law.

“Deport first, due process later" is Pres. Trump's M.O. Will U.S. citizens be asked 'show me your papers'? Will families be separated? Their zeal to deny immigrants due process & judicial review ensures mistakes will be made. This is cruelty in action.  https://t.co/BV5BRttT8j]

Imagine what we could achieve if @realDonaldTrump spent a fraction of the time fighting for working families that he does cooking up illegal schemes to punish families fleeing for a better life.  https://t.co/k3gDgAy5Gf
Hiding from the truth of what is happening to children and families is cowardly and a dereliction of duty. The Senate must investigate any and all claims of wrong-doing. We need a full hearing NOW.

This is Faviola and her son Dilan. They fled Honduras after MS-13 extorted money from her family, killed her grandfather, and threatened to kill her.  When they had no more money, they fled for their life.  This is who is coming to America seeking our help.  https://t.co/SHfMInFd6m

From the Donna Holding Facility, one of the sites you may remember from the Vice President’s now infamous border trip. This one holds children and families & was recently expanded to handle surge of detainees caused by Trump’s reckless and cruel separation/detention policies.  https://t.co/r3rnv23Osp

Things aren’t easy for working class families in Oregon, or around the country, which is why I just announced the “Good Jobs for 21st Century Energy Act” with @maziehirono, @SenTinaSmith, @AFLCIO’s @RichardTrumka, @NWF’s @EJinAction, & @BGAlliance’s Jessica Eckdish.  https://t.co/DrJyZs4OY3

column14: My sincere thanks to Fran for all she did on behalf of her entire community. My husband Verne and I send our condolences to the Tate family and friends during this difficult time. Attached is a clip of Fran on the Tonight Show w/ Johnny Carson in 1984.  https://t.co/7Zdt4TRFVg

Inadequate and overcrowded housing are major contributors to homelessness in rural Alaska. Any effort to promote the safety and wellness of Alaska Natives must include housing for families, homeless youth, and people fleeing domestic violence, sexual assault, and stalking.

AK Native women have reported rates of domestic violence up to 10x higher than in the rest of the U.S. and physical assault rates up to 12x higher. As we work to tackle these unacceptable statistics, FVPSA will help ensure victims & their children have the support they need.

@SenateDems The stakes are too high for us to stop fighting for patients and families. Democrats are going to continue calling on Republicans to stop attacking people's health care and start working with us to fix what they've been breaking—before it's too late.

@SenateDems While President Trump and Republicans have been using every tool they can to attack people’s health care, Democrats remain focused on seizing every opportunity we can to fight for patients and families and address the damage Republicans are doing.

54 years ago, President Johnson signed Medicare and Medicaid into law. Today, millions of patients and families—including seniors, people with disabilities, and more—rely on these programs for the affordable health care they need to live.

Summer meal programs are so important for families in WA & around the country—but there's more we must do to make sure the families who need this support are able to get it. That's why I'm working to pass legislation that would end summer hunger.  https://t.co/9XqclZkLs2

Republicans are pushing a partisan lawsuit to send your health care into chaos with NO PLAN for what to do if they win.    The clock is ticking, and families are watching closely. Republicans need to work with Democrats to fight for patients before it's too late. #ProtectOurCare  https://t.co/pi13iCPFpm

President Trump's #TitleX gag rule compromises health care for 4 million patients and undermines families' access to unbiased family planning services.   I led 43 other @SenateDems to urge the Trump administration to immediately rescind this harmful rule.   https://t.co/qvAQg5vz70

We must continue to fight so that millions of workers across the nation—especially women—are given a much deserved raise to support themselves and their families. RT if you agree that the Senate needs to pass the #RaiseTheWage Act.  https://t.co/HVKDVeIUnd

Republicans are back at it, trying to throw people's lives into chaos with a partisan lawsuit to scrap patient protections, strip millions of their health care, & send families' health costs skyrocketing. But they can expect just as much opposition as they saw two years ago.

Two years ago today, Congress narrowly defeated Trumpcare and stopped Republicans from gutting Medicaid, spiking families' premiums, and leaving people with pre-existing conditions back at the mercy of big insurance companies.

I will keep pressing the Trump Administration to make sure it is doing everything—everything—in its power to provide the proper resources, support, and care to children and families in U.S. custody.  https://t.co/f8wJpyGDL1

#TitleX is a historically bipartisan program that women and families turn to for a full range of confidential and unbiased family planning services. President Trump's gag rule undermines that care and should be immediately rescinded. #ProtectX  https://t.co/nkOD1Egv7v

If Republicans win their reckless, partisan lawsuit to strike down health care for millions of people, they have NO PLAN to ensure families and patients will still have access to the health care they need. I repeat—NO PLAN.  https://t.co/IrxVJF2AeO

I’m working with @SenatorLeahy to protect the rights of families and communities who live or travel near our national borders—because no one should be unnecessarily hassled or subject to warrantless searches.  https://t.co/EuLrbofIIT

Happy #NationalInternDay to my talented and hard-working interns on Capitol Hill and across Washington state! I'm always grateful for the young leaders who give their time and dedication to help me fight for families, patients, and the great people of Washington.  https://t.co/qoaEs3dZ91

Let’s be perfectly clear, Republicans have no plan for the patients who will lose coverage, no plan for the families who will see their health costs go up, and no plan for people nationwide who rely on protections for pre-existing conditions that would be taken away.

The 100-round magazine that allowed the Dayton shooter to fire 41 bullets in just 32 seconds was illegal in Ohio until the Republican-led state legislature began to roll back commonsense gun-safety laws. A federal ban on high-capacity magazines is long overdue.

The shooter in Dayton had a 100 round magazine that enabled him to fire 41 bullets in 32 seconds. Weapons capable of such damage should not be on our streets. The time to ban high capacity magazines is now.

A 100 round magazine allowed the Dayton shooter to fire 41 bullets in 32 seconds. High capacity magazines are unnecessary for hunting or home protection. They’re designed for one purpose: firing as many bullets as possible as fast as possible. They don’t belong on our streets.

In 2012, a domestic abuser shot & killed 3 women in Brookfield, WI, including his wife. He wounded 4 others, including a pregnant woman. The shooter, who bought the gun online w/o a background check, was prohibited from having a gun b/c of a domestic violence restraining order.

In 2014, a convicted felon shot & killed 4 people in Monongalia Co., WV, including his ex-girlfriend & her boyfriend. The shooter, who bought the gun online w/o a background check, was prohibited from having a gun b/c of a felony kidnapping conviction.

In 2015, a convicted felon shot & killed 8 people in Harris Co., TX: his ex-girlfriend, her husband & her 6 children. The shooter, who bought the gun online w/o a background check, was prohibited from having a gun b/c he was a convicted felon who’d spent nearly 12 yrs in prison.

There’s no logical reason why you must have a background check to buy from a retailer, but not online or at a gun show. The Manchin-Toomey background check bill will save lives. Had it been law, these mass shootings may never have occurred:
The shooter who attempted to murder brave Philadelphia police officers yesterday is a convicted felon who had no right to possess a firearm.

America’s wealthiest families continue to climb, while the middle-class is getting left behind.   It’s time to level the playing field and close loopholes in our tax code that allow millionaires and billionaires to get away without paying their fair share.

In 2017 alone, $3.8 TRILLION in assets, most of it held by millionaires and billionaires, went tax-free thanks to loopholes in our tax code.   It's time for the wealthy to start paying their fair share. My plan would level the playing field and give working families a fair shake.

America has a tale of two tax codes: the wealthy use games and tricks to avoid paying their fair share, while middle-class families play by the rules.  My proposal will fix our broken tax code and ensure that America's wealthiest pay their fair share.
